This product includes software developed by third parties:

- NVIDIA OpenShell (Apache-2.0)
  https://github.com/Mindpool-Labs/OpenShell
  Upstream (NVIDIA): the agent-sandbox governance layer — Landlock/seccomp/
  netns isolation, the L7 OPA policy engine, and the sandbox gateway.
  Consumed as the execution substrate on the confidential tier.

- Infrastacks OpenShell fork — PII detection + supply-chain enforcement
  (Apache-2.0; https://github.com/Mindpool-Labs/OpenShell)
  Infrastacks additions layered on NVIDIA's OpenShell:
    - openshell-pii          — the PII detection engine (healthcare IDs,
                               international IDs, financial IDs, driver
                               licenses, technical IDs; ~86 detector patterns)
    - openshell-pii-proxy    — the L7 privacy/PII-redaction proxy
    - openshell-supply-chain — the supply-chain policy enforcement engine
  Founding commits: 77e69a3, 86e1556, 000a108.
  Consumed by this runtime via the ne-privacy-router crate.

- AWS Firecracker (Apache-2.0)
  https://github.com/firecracker-microvm/firecracker
  The microVM and jailer substrate that provides per-workspace kernel
  isolation on the standard tier. Consumed as an upstream prebuilt
  binary (v1.16.0); this project does not modify Firecracker source.

A full dependency manifest with license texts is generated at build time
via `cargo metadata` and the `cargo deny` license check (see
`.github/workflows/ci.yml`).
